@page "/privacy"
<PageTitle>EggLedger - Privacy &amp; Cookies</PageTitle>
<main class="legal-page px-8 pt-6 pb-16 max-w-[860px] mx-auto overflow-y-auto">

    <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy &amp; Cookies</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated 6 July 2026</p>

    <div class="legal-disclaimer">
        EggLedger is an independent, fan-made tool and is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or
        sponsored by Auxbrain Inc. Egg, Inc. and related marks are the property of their respective
        owners.
    </div>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">The short version</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            EggLedger talks directly to the Egg, Inc. API. On desktop, all mission data stays on your
            own machine. There is no advertising, no third-party tracking, and no analytics. The only
            personal data stored anywhere is what Discord gives the service if you choose to turn on
            Settings Sync, and even then your settings themselves are encrypted before they leave your
            device. Payment data is never handled here.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Desktop app</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            The desktop build stores all config, mission data, and exports in the same directory as
            the EggLedger binary, in a local SQLite database and on-disk files. Nothing is uploaded
            anywhere. The only outbound network calls are to the Egg, Inc. API itself and an
            occasional update check against github.com, which carries no personal data. Unless you
            contact the operator directly or turn on Settings Sync, there is no way to know you're
            even using this tool.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Web app</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            The hosted web instance runs as a Blazor Server app: your browser holds a live connection
            to the server while you use it, and mission data is decoded and held server-side for that
            session in the same way the desktop app holds it locally. It is not sold, shared, or used
            for advertising.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Settings Sync (optional)</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            Settings Sync lets you carry your settings between devices. It is off unless you turn it
            on, and turning it on requires logging in with Discord. If you never use it, nothing about
            you leaves your machine beyond the Egg, Inc. API calls and the update check described
            above.
        </p>
        <p class="legal-p">
            If you do use it, your settings are encrypted client-side before upload. The encryption
            key is derived locally and never transmitted; the sync server receives and stores only an
            opaque encrypted blob it cannot read. Discord is used solely to verify your identity so
            the right blob comes back to the right device. No settings data passes through Discord's
            servers, and the service does not read your Discord email, messages, or server list, only
            the basic identity needed to recognise you again.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Cookies and local storage</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            The web app uses only strictly-necessary and functional storage. There are no advertising
            or tracking cookies, so there is no consent banner to click through. The storage used is:
        </p>
        <ul class="legal-list">
            <li>
                <strong>Session cookie.</strong> Keeps your Blazor Server circuit and, if you use
                Settings Sync, your Discord login connected across page loads. Removed when you log
                out or close the session.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Antiforgery token cookie.</strong> A security cookie that protects form
                submissions against cross-site request forgery. It does not identify you.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Browser local storage.</strong> Stores interface preferences you have chosen.
                It stays in your own browser and is never sent to a third party.
            </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="legal-p">
            The desktop app uses no cookies; its equivalent local settings live in the on-disk config
            described above.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Payments</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            Donations are processed entirely by third-party platforms (GitHub Sponsors, Patreon, and
            Buy Me a Coffee). This application never sees, processes, or stores your payment card
            data. Anything to do with billing is held by those platforms under their own privacy
            policies.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Data retention</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            Desktop data is retained for as long as you keep it on disk; deleting the app's directory
            removes it completely, with no system-level traces left behind. For Settings Sync, the
            encrypted blob is kept only while your sync account is active, and the service does not
            build a history of your activity for profiling purposes.
        </p>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Removing your data</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">To remove the data stored about you:</p>
        <ul class="legal-list">
            <li>Delete the EggLedger install directory to remove all local desktop data.</li>
            <li>
                Revoke EggLedger's access from your Discord account's authorized-apps settings to cut
                off Settings Sync.
            </li>
            <li>
                Clear your browser's cookies and local storage for the web app to remove the local
                items.
            </li>
            <li>
                Contact the operator through the
                <a class="legal-link" href="https://github.com/DavidArthurCole/EggLedger" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub repository</a>
                or the project
                <a class="legal-link" href="https://discord.davidarthurcole.me" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Discord server</a>
                to request deletion of your stored sync blob.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="legal-section">
        <h2 class="legal-h2">Changes</h2>
        <p class="legal-p">
            This policy may change as the project evolves. The date at the top reflects the latest
            version. For the terms that govern use of the service, see the
            <a class="legal-link" href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
        </p>
    </section>

</main>
